AB  - Alzheimer disease (AD), as one of the progressive neurodegenerative diseases, is recognized as one of the major causes of dementia throughout the world, and the existing methods of diagnosis and treatment prove to be highly limited. To overcome these obstacles, the proposed AD-TwinML framework integrates MRI and PET imaging with machine learning methods, which provides an effective solution to the diagnosis and management of Alzheimer. The proposed framework employes Vision transformer (ViTs), Digital twin (DT), and Time-series Transformers (TST) which will help in modeling disease progression to predict and diagnose Alzheimer’s. The experimental findings show that the framework has better accuracy (94.5%), sensitivity (91.5%), and AUC (0.946) than MM-CNN and MRIVGG16. Moreover, AD-TwinML has lower execution time (14 seconds) and error values (6.1%), which is appropriate to use in real time clinical scenarios. The framework is consistent with the objectives of Healthcare 5.0 because it facilitates consumer-focused, individualized monitoring and proactive intervention plans. © 2026 IEEE. All rights reserved.
